# Single-document indexing goes through `ingestDocument()`

`packages/sandbox/src/ingestDocument.ts` (`ingestDocument()`) is the single source
of truth for indexing ONE document: hash → idempotency check → `upsertDocument`
→ `deleteChunksForDocument` → `chunkMarkdown` → `embedBatch` → `insertChunks`.

## Invariant

- Any caller that needs to index a document (the CLI script
  `packages/sandbox/src/scripts/ingest.ts`, the admin API route under
  `packages/api/**`, future batch tools) MUST call `ingestDocument()`.
- Do NOT re-implement the chunk → embed → insert pipeline anywhere else. If the
  pipeline needs to change (metadata shape, hashing, idempotency rules), change
  it in `ingestDocument.ts` so every caller stays consistent.

## Boundaries

- `ingestDocument()` is pure-core: it does NOT read files, log to `console.*`, or
  catch errors. Callers own file/HTTP I/O, reporting, and error handling, and map
  the returned `IngestOutcome` (`indexed` / `skipped` / `empty`) to their own UX.
- Keep it that way: do not add filesystem or HTTP concerns to `ingestDocument.ts`.

## Cross-references

- Core: `packages/sandbox/src/ingestDocument.ts` (`ingestDocument`).
- Exported as `@max/sandbox/ingest` (see `packages/sandbox/package.json`).
- CLI caller: `packages/sandbox/src/scripts/ingest.ts`.
